timing_path_b...e_verbose_mode(25.10)    timing_path_b...e_verbose_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_path_based_enable_verbose_mode

Syntax
       timing_path_based_enable_verbose_mode <value >

       Default: 1

       Controls  printing  of  verbose messages during and at the end of path-
       based analysis (PBA).

       You can specify one of the three values - 0, 1, and 2.  These  are  de-
       scribed below:

              * 0:  Verbose  messages  are  not reported during exhaustive PBA
                analysis. For default PBA analysis, the path count will be re-
                ported.

              * 1: Reports the final message for PBA path count and max  depth
                reached  during  exhaustive PBA. Progress messages are not re-
                ported.

              * 2: Reports multiple progress messages after regular  intervals
                (in  addition  to the final message for PBA path count and max
                depth).

       This global variable impacts messages when the  report_timing  and  re-
       port_constraint commands are used in PBA mode.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

Examples
              * The  following  commands  print  messages during and after PBA
                analysis:

                set timing_path_based_enable_verbose_mode 2

                report_timing -retime path_slew_propagation  -retime_mode  ex-
                haustive -max_paths 500000 -nworst 1

                The  following  progress  messages  are  displayed  during PBA
                analysis:

                INFO:  Path  Based  Analysis  (PBA)  currently  performed   on
                '108455' paths

                INFO:   Path  Based  Analysis  (PBA)  currently  performed  on
                '217574' paths

                INFO:  Path  Based  Analysis  (PBA)  currently  performed   on
                '327511' paths

                INFO:   Path  Based  Analysis  (PBA)  currently  performed  on
                '437472' paths

                ....

                The following messages are displayed at the end of PBA  analy-
                sis mentioning the PBA path count and max depth reached during
                exhaustive PBA:

                INFO:  Path  Based Analysis (PBA) performed on total '2660526'
                paths

                INFO:   Max    depth    9460    reached    for    end    point
                'top/hier1/hier2/flop/d' during Path Based Analysis

